PrecisDecision of the Governor in Council, having considered the petition of the Stentor telephone companies (a) to vary TELECOM DECISION CRTC 95-21 rendered by the Canadian Radio-television and Telecommunications Commission so that the said companies will not have to decrease basic long distance rates as part of the rate rebalancing plan, and (b) to deny the request of AGT Limited and the counter petition of PATS.
